%N A385742 Decimal expansion of (Pi/32) * (-1/2- zeta'(4/3)/zeta(4/3)).
%C A385742 Let epsilon = 1/3, then the constant appears to be equal to: (Pi/32) * (4 + 1/((epsilon-1)*epsilon) - zeta'(1 + epsilon)/zeta(1 + epsilon)) = Integral_{t=0..oo} (1 - 12*t^2)/((1 + 4*t^2)^3) * Integral_{sigma=1/2..oo} Re(log(zeta(sigma + epsilon + i*t))) dsigma dt. Verified up to 9 decimal digits. - _Mats Granvik_, Jul 08 2025, Jul 18 2026
%H A385742 Mats Granvik, <a href="https://mathematica.stackexchange.com/q/314159/328">How do you increase the precision and accuracy of the numerical approximation of the Volchkov integral?</a>
%e A385742 0.1943911932990676252341639336900663506249738278660...
%t A385742 epsilon = 1/3; s = 1 + epsilon; RealDigits[Pi/32*(4 + 1/((-2 + s)*(-1 + s)) - Zeta'[s]/ Zeta[s]), 10, 105][[1]]
